The paper deals with the problem of phase retrieval, which is a topic in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of various algorithms for solving the phase retrieval problem, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of Gaussian random matrices, which is a topic in numerical analysis, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper presents theoretical guarantees for the performance of the algorithms, which falls under the scope of cs.SI (Systems and Control).
